---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const testimonials = (await getCollection('testimonials')).sort(
  (a, b) => a.data.order - b.data.order
);
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Product designer focused on clarity, systems, and thoughtful delivery in complex domains."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-10 md:grid-cols-3 md:gap-12 md:items-start">
      <header class="max-w-prose md:col-span-2 md:min-w-0">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-stone-900 leading-tight">Hello again!</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
          In my job I love most solving hard problems and reimaigning old solutions to fit new needs. Ant time it is possible, I rely on reaserch and analytical data. This
          approach is rooted in my background in biology, where understanding cause and effect is essential.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
          I’m particularly interested in health and finance products.
          I don’t come from these industries directly, but my background in biology (lab and academic work) and personal experience with investing make me especially interested in these areas.
                  </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
          <span class="font-bold text-stone-800">Gallup Top 10:</span>
          Input · Restorative · Intellection · Individualization · Learner · Achiever · Self-Assurance ·
          Arranger · Futuristic · Analytical
        </p>
      </header>
      <div class="w-full min-w-0 shrink-0 md:col-span-1">
        <img
          src="/photo-taiwan.JPG"
          alt="Outdoor portrait in Taiwan"
          width="1645"
          height="1537"
          class="w-full max-w-full rounded-lg border border-stone-200 object-cover aspect-[1645/1537] shadow-sm"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="mt-16 md:mt-20" aria-labelledby="about-superpowers-heading">
      <h2 id="about-superpowers-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-stone-900">
        My superpowers
      </h2>
      <ul class="mt-10 grid gap-10 md:gap-12 md:grid-cols-3">
        <li class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-stone-900">Initiative</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">I don’t wait for tasks – I propose them.

            I often bring ideas together with a first version of a solution. For example, I introduced the ORCA framework for more complex projects and started experimenting with AI-supported research.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-stone-900">End-to-end thinking</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">I care about how things actually work, not just how they look.

            I can read HTML and CSS, and I enjoy learning how things are built. Recently, I’ve been exploring vibe coding – this portfolio is one of the results.
        <li class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-stone-900">UX writing</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">As a former editor, I focus on clarity, structure, and plain language.

            In my current role, I introduced AI assistants to help teams maintain consistent Tone of Voice and improve accessibility.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16 md:mt-20" aria-labelledby="about-values-heading">
      <h2 id="about-values-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-stone-900">
        Values
      </h2>
      <ul class="mt-10 grid gap-10 md:gap-12 md:grid-cols-3">
        <li class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-stone-900">Clarity & direction</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">Everything becomes easier when you know where you’re going.

            I work best when there is a clear goal, whether I define it myself or we define it as a team.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-stone-900">Learning &amp; Growth</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
            It may sound cliché, but I take it seriously. Without continuous learning, there is no progress. In biology, this is known as the Red Queen effect – you have to keep moving just to stay in place.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-stone-900">Purpose</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">I want my work to matter.

            I’m looking for problems worth solving and products aligned with my values. For example, I wouldn’t be a good fit for betting platforms or non-sustainable e-commerce.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mt-16 md:mt-24 border-t border-stone-200 pt-16 md:pt-20"
      aria-labelledby="about-story-heading"
    >
      <h2 id="about-story-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-stone-900">
        Story
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-prose text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
        Visual showcase of my career — milestones, roles, and moments worth highlighting.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 gap-10 sm:grid-cols-2 md:gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {
          ['Chapter one', 'Chapter two', 'Chapter three'].map((label) => (
            <li class="space-y-3">
              <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-500">{label}</p>
              <div
                class="flex aspect-[4/3] items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-dashed border-stone-300 bg-stone-50 text-base text-stone-500"
                aria-hidden="true"
              >
                Image placeholder
              </div>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mt-16 md:mt-24 border-t border-stone-200 pt-16 md:pt-20"
      aria-labelledby="about-testimonials-heading"
    >
      <h2 id="about-testimonials-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-stone-900">
        What it’s like to work with me
      </h2>
      <ul class="mt-10 grid gap-12 md:gap-14 md:grid-cols-3">
        {
          testimonials.map((t) => (
            <li>
              <blockquote class="space-y-6">
                <p class="font-serif text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-800">
                  “{t.data.quote}”
                </p>
                <footer class="text-base text-stone-600">
                  <cite class="not-italic font-medium text-stone-800">{t.data.author}</cite>
                  <span class="block mt-1">
                    {t.data.role}
                    {t.data.company && ` · ${t.data.company}`}
                  </span>
                </footer>
              </blockquote>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-16 md:mt-20">
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/karolina-stachowiak/details/recommendations/?detailScreenTabIndex=0"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="group inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-base font-medium text-stone-900 transition-colors"
        >
          <span class="underline underline-offset-4 decoration-stone-400 group-hover:decoration-stone-700">
            Show more on Linkedin
          </span>
          <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mt-16 md:mt-24 border-t border-stone-200 pt-16 md:pt-20"
      aria-labelledby="about-people-heading"
    >
      <h2 id="about-people-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-stone-900">
        People
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-prose text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
        I care about how teams work together. I regularly organize small seasonal gatherings for my team to
        strengthen collaboration, trust, and communication. From time to time, I also invite colleagues from
        outside the organization, turning meetings into informal meetups.
      </p>
      <div
        class="mt-8 flex max-w-3xl aspect-video items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-dashed border-stone-300 bg-stone-50 text-base text-stone-500"
      >
        Video placeholder
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
